; A `:merge` body must be a pure write, so reading another
; (non-constructor) function in it is a live-DB read that
; seminaive execution can't track. It is rejected at
; typecheck in all modes (LookupInMergeDisallowed).
;
; Reading `foo` in `bar`'s merge below is such a read.

(function foo () i64 :no-merge)

(function bar () i64 :merge (foo))
